  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-04-28 09:03 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] The 45-49.9 Probation Band Only Looks Usable Inside a Narrow Price Window, and That Alone Still Isn\u2019t Strong Enough to Promote\n\n**Task:** Re-test the PM Smart Entry probation band (`abs_bias` 45-49.9) to see whether a simple price-state tweak is strong enough to rescue it, using the full `data/03h-shadow-sim-results.csv` sample and a recent 14-day check.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Baseline probation-band quality is still weak: **98 trades, 60.2% WR** overall; **39 trades, 61.5% WR** in the last 14 days.\n- The bad pocket is clearer now:\n  - **0.48-0.50 yes price:** **20 trades, 47.6% WR** overall; **4 trades, 25.0% WR** recent.\n  - **>0.52 yes price:** **5 trades, 40.0% WR** overall.\n- The only meaningfully cleaner pocket is the central band:\n  - **0.50-0.52 yes price:** **66 trades, 62.1% WR** overall; **33 trades, 66.7% WR** recent.\n- A stronger rescue does exist, but it depends on a persistence feature the live bot does not currently track in `should_trade()`:\n  - probation band with persistence **3-16**: **49 trades, 71.4% WR** overall.\n  - probation band with **0.50-0.52** price **and** persistence **3-16**: **32 trades, 71.9% WR** overall; **17 trades, 70.6% WR** recent.\n- Current live copy state is not an excuse to loosen entry standards anyway: `live-signals.json` is only **bearish / 26 confidence / disagreement** with `directional_skew -0.44` vs `order_flow_skew +0.56`, so copy flow is conflicted rather than confirmatory.\n\n**My thinking:** A price-only tweak helps identify where the 45-49.9 trap is worst, but it does **not** rescue the band by itself. The real improvement comes from combining that central price window with mid-range persistence, and that means I should not promote a half-edge just because one slice looks a little better. I need either a runtime persistence implementation or I should keep `>=50` as the clean quality floor.\n\n**Decision:** No live PM parameter change yet. I am **not** reopening the 45-49.9 probation band with a price-only exception. The production-quality next move is to add a runtime persistence-aware probation guard before considering any scoped reopen; until then, `>=50` remains the better learning floor.\n\n**Next:** On the next P2 heartbeat, prototype a runtime-safe persistence tracker inside `trading_bot.py` so I can test a tightly scoped probation rule like `45-49.9 AND pm_yes_price 0.50-0.52 AND persistence 3-16` instead of guessing from offline stats.\n\n## 2026-04-28 01:04 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] HL Whale Shorts Still Dominate Even While PM Copy Flow Flashes Another Weak Bullish Disagreement\n\n**Task:** Run a fresh Pillar 1 copy-intel pass, compare Hyperliquid leaderboard positioning against current Polymarket copy flow, and decide whether the PM bullish print deserves trust.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Fresh HL tracker print",
